stions. Do NOT repeat section instructions. •\tDo NOT print word-count references.  •\tDo NOT print “≈180 words”. •\tDo NOT mention constraints. •\tDo NOT describe formatting rules.  •\tDo NOT mention this prompt.  •\tOutput must look like a professional final report — not a questionnaire response.   •\tLength Constraint (Internal Only): •\tEach question must be answered in substantial depth, approximately equivalent to 180 words.  •\tThis is an internal writing constraint and must NOT appear in output. •\tDo not compress sections. •\tDo not skip sections. •\tDo not merge answers.  •\tAvoid:  •\tVague generalizations •\tHype language •\tMotivational tone •\tFiller Fabricated data •\tRepetitive phrasing •\tAssume full real-world execution visualization:  •\tcapital, •\thiring,  •\tcompetition, •\tcompliance, •\tdistribution,  •\teconomics.  •\tUse:  Market structure reasoning. •\tEconomic logic Behavioral  •\tfriction analysis  •\tCapital cycle awareness  •\tCompetitive positioning •\tRisk mapping System design clarity  Tone:  •\tDirect. Structured.  •\tAnalytical. •\tGrounded. •\tInstitutional. •\tEnd with:  •\tExecutive Summary •\tClear Recommendation •\tKey Risks •\tKey Leverage Points  •\tNo instruction text.  •\tOnly analysis.  •\tAssume we have full global market awareness and historical context of similar ventures. •\tOutput must be: •\tDo NOT print word-count references.  •\tDo NOT print “≈180 words”. •\tDo NOT mention constraints. •\tDo NOT describe formatting rules.  •\tDo NOT mention this prompt.  •\tOutput must look like a professional final report — not a questionnaire response.   •\tLength Constraint (Internal Only):  •\tDeep  •\tBrief where possible but thorough  •\tHighly structured  •\tFounder-grade  •\tInvestor-grade  •\tNo irrelevant text  •\tNo filler  •\tNo emojis  •\tNo marketing language  •\tAlways score where requested (0–10).\nhIGHLITED EACH HEADING IN PROPER STRUCTURED THEN EXPLANATION\n"
