              "type": "HumanMessagePromptTemplate",
              "message": "Perform a full institutional-grade analysis of the following startup idea:  [INSERT STARTUP IDEA HERE]  Write a structured, professional final report.  Do NOT:  Mention word counts. Repeat questions. Mention formatting instructions. Mention internal constraints. Add irrelevant commentary.  Follow the structure below strictly, but present it as a finished report, not a questionnaire. \n 1️⃣ IDEA DECONSTRUCTION :\n 1 What the idea is \n 2 What it is not Boundaries Scope realism \n 3 Painkiller vs vitamin vs status Behavioral change requirement\n 4 Incremental vs disruptive Capital intensity \n 5 Time-to-market realism Founder dependency  6 Clarity Score (0–10) with reasoning.\n\n 2️⃣ PROBLEM SPACE DEEP DIVE: 1.\texplain Root cause Structural vs surface problem  2.\t explain Frequency Severity Economic 3.\t explain cost Urgency 4.\t explain Who suffers 5.\t explain Who pays  6.\t explain Who benefits from status quo Growth trajectory Macro tailwinds/headwinds  7.\texplain Current substitutes Problem Reality Score (0–10) 3️⃣ HISTORICAL & PRECEDENT ANALYSIS : •\t1 explain Comparable startups Failure patterns Success patterns . •\t2 explain  What changed now Technology shifts. •\t3 explain Regulatory shifts. •\t4 explain Distribution shifts.  •\t5 explain Cost structure shifts. •\t6 explain Structural industry lessons. •\t7explain Capital cycle patterns. •\t8explain  Founder underestimation risks. 4️⃣ POWER STRUCTURE ANALYSIS :\n 1explain  Incumbent dominance \n 2 explain Regulatory barriers \n 3 explain Platform dependency  4 explain Supplier power 5 explain Customer power  6 explain Switching cost reality 7 explain Network control  8 explain  Data ownership  9  explain Capital barriers  10 explain Market openness 11 explain Leverage control points  5️⃣ ACADEMIC / TECHNICAL FOUNDATIONS :  1 explain Scientific feasibility  2explain  Engineering complexity 3 explain Data dependency 4 explain Infrastructure Scalability constraints  5 explain Compliance risk  6 explain Security risk  7 explain Privacy risk  8 explain Science vs execution risk  9 explain Operational fragility  6️⃣ SOLUTION ARCHITECTURE & SYSTEM DESIGN  1 explain Workflow Core components.  2 explain Data logic Human vs automation   Feedback loops Defensibility Scalability model. 3 explain Cost curve Unit economics Bottlenecks Failure modes.  7️⃣ PROBLEM–SOLUTION FIT : explain User disappointment risk Workarounds Willingness to pay Budget clarity Validation signals Retention likelihood Habit formation. Expansion potential Fit Score (0–10).   8️ TARGET USER & DISTRIBUTION REALITY: 1explain ICP User vs buyer Decision maker.  2 explain Decision cycle . 3explain  Behavioural inertia.  4explain Status quo bias.  5 explain Switching friction \n. 6 explain Distribution channels.  7 explain CAC risk.  8 explain Trust barrier.  9 explain Network growth potential.  10explain Founder-led sales need Segment realism ."
