              "type": "HumanMessagePromptTemplate",
              "message": "=Perform a full institutional-grade analysis of the following startup idea:  [INSERT STARTUP IDEA HERE]  Write a structured, professional final report.  Do NOT:  Mention word counts. Repeat questions. Mention formatting instructions. Mention internal constraints. Add irrelevant commentary.  Follow the structure below strictly, but present it as a finished report, not a questionnaire.\n\nPerform a full institutional-grade analysis of the following startup idea:  [INSERT STARTUP IDEA HERE]  Write a structured, professional final report.  Do NOT:  Mention word counts. Repeat questions. Mention formatting instructions. Mention internal constraints. Add irrelevant commentary.  Follow the structure below strictly, but present it as a finished report, not a questionnaire.\n9️⃣ DISTRIBUTION & GTM REALITY : \n1.\tEXPALIN Acquisition channels CAC estimate (qualitative if unknown) \n2.\tEXPALIN LTV estimate (qualitative if unknown) \n3.\tEXPALIN Sales cycle \n4.\tEXPALIN Founder sales capability Channel scalability \n5.\tEXPALIN Paid dependency\n6.\tEXPALIN Platform reliance risk\n7.\tEXPALIN Organic loop Distribution Score (0–10)\n\n🔟 RETENTION & ENGAGEMENT MODEL:\n1.\tEXPALIN Usage frequency.\n2.\tEXPALIN Switching cost.\n3.\tEXPALIN Data lock-in.\n4.\tEXPALIN Network effects. \n5.\tEXPALIN Habit loops Built-in stickiness.\n\n1️⃣1️⃣ COMPETITIVE LANDSCAPE :\n1.\tEXPALIN Direct competitors. \n2.\tEXPALIN Indirect substitutes VC challengers Incumbents.\n3.\tEXPALIN Price war risk.\n4.\tEXPALIN Feature parity risk .\n5.\tEXPALIN Market saturation.\n\n1️⃣2️⃣ UNIQUE VALUE PROPOSITION —\n1.\tEXPALIN STRESS TEST 10x or 10% better? \n2.\tEXPALIN Tech moat.\n3.\tEXPALIN Brand moat \n4.\tEXPALIN Network moat\n5.\tEXPALIN Distribution moat \n6.\tEXPALIN Speed advantage\n7.\tEXPALIN Copy risk Defensibility Score (0–10)\n\n1️⃣3️⃣ MARKET DEPTH & ECONOMIC VIABILITY\n1.\tEXPALIN Realistic TAM CAGR \n2.\tEXPALIN Budget availability\n3.\tEXPALIN Try vs pay gap Venture